90 times per second

28
00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:13.000
B 190 times per second

29
00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:17.000
Or see two hundred and ninety times per second

30
00:02:17.000 --> 00:02:24.000
Well, I have absolutely no idea so I'm going to guess a hundred and ninety times per second

31
00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
Okay, well we'll find out the answer later in the programme

32
00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:36.000
We've been talking about honey bees but these are just one of the twenty thousand species of bee which exist around the world

33
00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:42.000
In fact, honey bees are one of the most widespread insects on the planet and not endangered at all

34
00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:48.000
But the picture isn't so good for wild bees including the Bumblebee

35
00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
As biologist Dave Galson from the University of Sussex

36
00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
Explain to BBC World Service programme crowd science

37
00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:01.000
In the UK we have twenty six Bumblebee species but three of gone extinct

38
00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:06.000
Many of the others and I cling on in little isolated pockets of good habitat

39
00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:09.000
Honey bees have beekeepers to look after them

40
00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:12.000
But nobody's looking out for the wild bees

41
00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:16.000
Three of the twenty six species of British Bumblebee have gone extinct

42
00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:22.000
And Dave says other species are clinging on meaning barely continuing to survive with great effort

43
00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:30.000
This happens in isolated pockets small areas of habitat in which a particular insect or animal can survive

44
00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:36.000
So while honey bees may not be endangered, lots of other bee species are

45
00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:43.000
And this is bad news because we rely on insects to pollinate crops and to keep ecosystems functioning

46
00:03:43.000 --> 00:03:49.000
That's right, Beth 87% of all plants species need insects for pollination

47
00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:55.000
So without them, most plants on earth would disappear which would obviously be catastrophic

48
00:03:55.000 --> 00:04:02.000
But according to Dave Galson, pollination is just one of the many things bees do for us

49
00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:06.000
As he explained to BBC World Services crowd science

50
00:04:06.000 --> 00:04:09.000
That isn't the only thing that insects are doing

51
00:04:09.000 --> 00:04:15.000
And there are much less glamorous less well known things like recycling, k-poop

52
00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:20.000
And helping to keep the soil healthy and helping to control crop pests and so on

53
00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:27.000
All of which are also really important and we kind of take them for granted or just oblivious that they're even happening

54
00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:35.000
Recycling, k-poop and keeping the soil healthy are two important jobs bees do which we take for granted

55
00:04:35.000 --> 00:04:41.000
If you take something for granted, you've failed to value or appreciate something which benefits you

56
00:04:41.000 --> 00:04:50.000
We humans are oblivious, meaning unaware or unmindful of the many things bees do to support life on earth

57
00:04:50.000 --> 00:04:54.000
So while eating more honey, probably won't do much to save wild bees

58
00:04:54.000 --> 00:05:00.000
There are things you can do such as growing bee friendly plants which flower in spring like lavender

59
00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.000
Okay Phil, I think it's time to reveal the answer to my question

60
00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:10.000
I asked you how many times bees flap their wings per second

61
00:05:10.000 --> 00:05:15.000
You said 190 which was the correct answer well done

62
00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:23.000
Okay, let's recap the vocabulary we've learnt starting with vegan someone who doesn't consume any animal products

63
00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:30.000
If you say there's a question mark around something, you mean there's some doubt or uncertainty about it

64
00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:37.000
If an animal species is clinging on, it's holding onto existence with great effort

65
00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:43.000
I selected pockets refer to small areas of habitat in which a particular insect or animal can survive

66
00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:50.000
To take something for granted means to not appreciate or show gratitude for something which helps you

67
00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:54.000
And finally the adjective oblivious means unaware

